214bool
215dns_name_isvalid(const dns_name_t *name) {
216 unsigned char *ndata, *offsets;
217 unsigned int offset, count, length, nlabels;
218
219 if (!VALID_NAME(name))
220 return (false);
221
222 if (name->length > 255U || name->labels > 127U)
223 return (false);
224
225 ndata = name->ndata;
226 length = name->length;
227 offsets = name->offsets;
228 offset = 0;
229 nlabels = 0;
230
231 while (offset != length) {
232 count = *ndata;
233 if (count > 63U)
234 return (false);
235 if (offsets != NULL && offsets[nlabels] != offset)
236 return (false);
237
238 nlabels++;
239 offset += count + 1;
240 ndata += count + 1;
241 if (offset > length)
242 return (false);
243
244 if (count == 0)
245 break;
246 }
247
248 if (nlabels != name->labels || offset != name->length)
249 return (false);
250
251 return (true);
252}

295#define hyphenchar(c) ((c) == 0x2d)
296#define asterchar(c) ((c) == 0x2a)
297#define alphachar(c) (((c) >= 0x41 && (c) <= 0x5a) \
298 || ((c) >= 0x61 && (c) <= 0x7a))
299#define digitchar(c) ((c) >= 0x30 && (c) <= 0x39)
300#define borderchar(c) (alphachar(c) || digitchar(c))
301#define middlechar(c) (borderchar(c) || hyphenchar(c))
302#define domainchar(c) ((c) > 0x20 && (c) < 0x7f)

304bool
305dns_name_ismailbox(const dns_name_t *name) {
306 unsigned char *ndata, ch;
307 unsigned int n;
308 bool first;
309
310 REQUIRE(VALID_NAME(name));
311 REQUIRE(name->labels > 0);
312 REQUIRE(name->attributes & DNS_NAMEATTR_ABSOLUTE);
313
314 /*
315 * Root label.
316 */
317 if (name->length == 1)
318 return (true);
319
320 ndata = name->ndata;
321 n = *ndata++;
322 INSIST(n <= 63);
323 while (n--) {
324 ch = *ndata++;
325 if (!domainchar(ch))
326 return (false);
327 }
328
329 if (ndata == name->ndata + name->length)
330 return (false);
331
332 /*
333 * RFC952/RFC1123 hostname.
334 */
335 while (ndata < (name->ndata + name->length)) {
336 n = *ndata++;
337 INSIST(n <= 63);
338 first = true;
339 while (n--) {
340 ch = *ndata++;
341 if (first || n == 0) {
342 if (!borderchar(ch))
343 return (false);
344 } else {
345 if (!middlechar(ch))
346 return (false);
347 }
348 first = false;
349 }
350 }
351 return (true);
352}

354bool
355dns_name_ishostname(const dns_name_t *name, bool wildcard) {
356 unsigned char *ndata, ch;
357 unsigned int n;
358 bool first;
359
360 REQUIRE(VALID_NAME(name));
361 REQUIRE(name->labels > 0);
362 REQUIRE(name->attributes & DNS_NAMEATTR_ABSOLUTE);
363
364 /*
365 * Root label.
366 */
367 if (name->length == 1)
368 return (true);
369
370 /*
371 * Skip wildcard if this is a ownername.
372 */
373 ndata = name->ndata;
374 if (wildcard && ndata[0] == 1 && ndata[1] == '*')
375 ndata += 2;
376
377 /*
378 * RFC292/RFC1123 hostname.
379 */
380 while (ndata < (name->ndata + name->length)) {
381 n = *ndata++;
382 INSIST(n <= 63);
383 first = true;
384 while (n--) {
385 ch = *ndata++;
386 if (first || n == 0) {
387 if (!borderchar(ch))
388 return (false);
389 } else {
390 if (!middlechar(ch))
391 return (false);
392 }
393 first = false;
394 }
395 }
396 return (true);
397}

419bool
420dns_name_internalwildcard(const dns_name_t *name) {
421 unsigned char *ndata;
422 unsigned int count;
423 unsigned int label;
424
425 /*
426 * Does 'name' contain a internal wildcard?
427 */
428
429 REQUIRE(VALID_NAME(name));
430 REQUIRE(name->labels > 0);
431
432 /*
433 * Skip first label.
434 */
435 ndata = name->ndata;
436 count = *ndata++;
437 INSIST(count <= 63);
438 ndata += count;
439 label = 1;
440 /*
441 * Check all but the last of the remaining labels.
442 */
443 while (label + 1 < name->labels) {
444 count = *ndata++;
445 INSIST(count <= 63);
446 if (count == 1 && *ndata == '*')
447 return (true);
448 ndata += count;
449 label++;
450 }
451 return (false);
452}

457

488dns_namereln_t
489dns_name_fullcompare(const dns_name_t *name1, const dns_name_t *name2,
490 int *orderp, unsigned int *nlabelsp)
491{
492 unsigned int l1, l2, l, count1, count2, count, nlabels;
493 int cdiff, ldiff, chdiff;
494 unsigned char *label1, *label2;
495 unsigned char *offsets1, *offsets2;
496 dns_offsets_t odata1, odata2;
497 dns_namereln_t namereln = dns_namereln_none;
498
499 /*
500 * Determine the relative ordering under the DNSSEC order relation of
501 * 'name1' and 'name2', and also determine the hierarchical
502 * relationship of the names.
503 *
504 * Note: It makes no sense for one of the names to be relative and the
505 * other absolute. If both names are relative, then to be meaningfully
506 * compared the caller must ensure that they are both relative to the
507 * same domain.
508 */
509
510 REQUIRE(VALID_NAME(name1));
511 REQUIRE(VALID_NAME(name2));
512 REQUIRE(orderp != NULL);
513 REQUIRE(nlabelsp != NULL);
514 /*
515 * Either name1 is absolute and name2 is absolute, or neither is.
516 */
517 REQUIRE((name1->attributes & DNS_NAMEATTR_ABSOLUTE) ==
518 (name2->attributes & DNS_NAMEATTR_ABSOLUTE));
519
520 if (ISC_UNLIKELY(name1 == name2)) {
521 *orderp = 0;
522 *nlabelsp = name1->labels;
523 return (dns_namereln_equal);
524 }
525
526 SETUP_OFFSETS(name1, offsets1, odata1);
527 SETUP_OFFSETS(name2, offsets2, odata2);
528
529 nlabels = 0;
530 l1 = name1->labels;
531 l2 = name2->labels;
532 if (l2 > l1) {
533 l = l1;
534 ldiff = 0 - (l2 - l1);
535 } else {
536 l = l2;
537 ldiff = l1 - l2;
538 }
539
540 offsets1 += l1;
541 offsets2 += l2;
542
543 while (ISC_LIKELY(l > 0)) {
544 l--;
545 offsets1--;
546 offsets2--;
547 label1 = &name1->ndata[*offsets1];
548 label2 = &name2->ndata[*offsets2];
549 count1 = *label1++;
550 count2 = *label2++;
551
552 /*
553 * We dropped bitstring labels, and we don't support any
554 * other extended label types.
555 */
556 INSIST(count1 <= 63 && count2 <= 63);
557
558 cdiff = (int)count1 - (int)count2;
559 if (cdiff < 0)
560 count = count1;
561 else
562 count = count2;
563
564 /* Loop unrolled for performance */
565 while (ISC_LIKELY(count > 3)) {
566 chdiff = (int)maptolower[label1[0]] -
567 (int)maptolower[label2[0]];
568 if (chdiff != 0) {
569 *orderp = chdiff;
570 goto done;
571 }
572 chdiff = (int)maptolower[label1[1]] -
573 (int)maptolower[label2[1]];
574 if (chdiff != 0) {
575 *orderp = chdiff;
576 goto done;
577 }
578 chdiff = (int)maptolower[label1[2]] -
579 (int)maptolower[label2[2]];
580 if (chdiff != 0) {
581 *orderp = chdiff;
582 goto done;
583 }
584 chdiff = (int)maptolower[label1[3]] -
585 (int)maptolower[label2[3]];
586 if (chdiff != 0) {
587 *orderp = chdiff;
588 goto done;
589 }
590 count -= 4;
591 label1 += 4;
592 label2 += 4;
593 }
594 while (ISC_LIKELY(count-- > 0)) {
595 chdiff = (int)maptolower[*label1++] -
596 (int)maptolower[*label2++];
597 if (chdiff != 0) {
598 *orderp = chdiff;
599 goto done;
600 }
601 }
602 if (cdiff != 0) {
603 *orderp = cdiff;
604 goto done;
605 }
606 nlabels++;
607 }
608
609 *orderp = ldiff;
610 if (ldiff < 0)
611 namereln = dns_namereln_contains;
612 else if (ldiff > 0)
613 namereln = dns_namereln_subdomain;
614 else
615 namereln = dns_namereln_equal;
616 *nlabelsp = nlabels;
617 return (namereln);
618
619 done:
620 *nlabelsp = nlabels;
621 if (nlabels > 0)
622 namereln = dns_namereln_commonancestor;
623
624 return (namereln);
625}

627int
628dns_name_compare(const dns_name_t *name1, const dns_name_t *name2) {
629 int order;
630 unsigned int nlabels;
631
632 /*
633 * Determine the relative ordering under the DNSSEC order relation of
634 * 'name1' and 'name2'.
635 *
636 * Note: It makes no sense for one of the names to be relative and the
637 * other absolute. If both names are relative, then to be meaningfully
638 * compared the caller must ensure that they are both relative to the
639 * same domain.
640 */
641
642 (void)dns_name_fullcompare(name1, name2, &order, &nlabels);
643
644 return (order);
645}

647bool
648dns_name_equal(const dns_name_t *name1, const dns_name_t *name2) {
649 unsigned int l, count;
650 unsigned char c;
651 unsigned char *label1, *label2;
652
653 /*
654 * Are 'name1' and 'name2' equal?
655 *
656 * Note: It makes no sense for one of the names to be relative and the
657 * other absolute. If both names are relative, then to be meaningfully
658 * compared the caller must ensure that they are both relative to the
659 * same domain.
660 */
661
662 REQUIRE(VALID_NAME(name1));
663 REQUIRE(VALID_NAME(name2));
664 /*
665 * Either name1 is absolute and name2 is absolute, or neither is.
666 */
667 REQUIRE((name1->attributes & DNS_NAMEATTR_ABSOLUTE) ==
668 (name2->attributes & DNS_NAMEATTR_ABSOLUTE));
669
670 if (ISC_UNLIKELY(name1 == name2))
671 return (true);
672
673 if (name1->length != name2->length)
674 return (false);
675
676 l = name1->labels;
677
678 if (l != name2->labels)
679 return (false);
680
681 label1 = name1->ndata;
682 label2 = name2->ndata;
683 while (ISC_LIKELY(l-- > 0)) {
684 count = *label1++;
685 if (count != *label2++)
686 return (false);
687
688 INSIST(count <= 63); /* no bitstring support */
689
690 /* Loop unrolled for performance */
691 while (ISC_LIKELY(count > 3)) {
692 c = maptolower[label1[0]];
693 if (c != maptolower[label2[0]])
694 return (false);
695 c = maptolower[label1[1]];
696 if (c != maptolower[label2[1]])
697 return (false);
698 c = maptolower[label1[2]];
699 if (c != maptolower[label2[2]])
700 return (false);
701 c = maptolower[label1[3]];
702 if (c != maptolower[label2[3]])
703 return (false);
704 count -= 4;
705 label1 += 4;
706 label2 += 4;
707 }
708 while (ISC_LIKELY(count-- > 0)) {
709 c = maptolower[*label1++];
710 if (c != maptolower[*label2++])
711 return (false);
712 }
713 }
714
715 return (true);
716}
717
718bool
719dns_name_caseequal(const dns_name_t *name1, const dns_name_t *name2) {
720
721 /*
722 * Are 'name1' and 'name2' equal?
723 *
724 * Note: It makes no sense for one of the names to be relative and the
725 * other absolute. If both names are relative, then to be meaningfully
726 * compared the caller must ensure that they are both relative to the
727 * same domain.
728 */
729
730 REQUIRE(VALID_NAME(name1));
731 REQUIRE(VALID_NAME(name2));
732 /*
733 * Either name1 is absolute and name2 is absolute, or neither is.
734 */
735 REQUIRE((name1->attributes & DNS_NAMEATTR_ABSOLUTE) ==
736 (name2->attributes & DNS_NAMEATTR_ABSOLUTE));
737
738 if (name1->length != name2->length)
739 return (false);
740
741 if (memcmp(name1->ndata, name2->ndata, name1->length) != 0)
742 return (false);
743
744 return (true);
745}
746
747int
748dns_name_rdatacompare(const dns_name_t *name1, const dns_name_t *name2) {
749 unsigned int l1, l2, l, count1, count2, count;
750 unsigned char c1, c2;
751 unsigned char *label1, *label2;
752
753 /*
754 * Compare two absolute names as rdata.
755 */
756
757 REQUIRE(VALID_NAME(name1));
758 REQUIRE(name1->labels > 0);
759 REQUIRE((name1->attributes & DNS_NAMEATTR_ABSOLUTE) != 0);
760 REQUIRE(VALID_NAME(name2));
761 REQUIRE(name2->labels > 0);
762 REQUIRE((name2->attributes & DNS_NAMEATTR_ABSOLUTE) != 0);
763
764 l1 = name1->labels;
765 l2 = name2->labels;
766
767 l = (l1 < l2) ? l1 : l2;
768
769 label1 = name1->ndata;
770 label2 = name2->ndata;
771 while (l > 0) {
772 l--;
773 count1 = *label1++;
774 count2 = *label2++;
775
776 /* no bitstring support */
777 INSIST(count1 <= 63 && count2 <= 63);
778
779 if (count1 != count2)
780 return ((count1 < count2) ? -1 : 1);
781 count = count1;
782 while (count > 0) {
783 count--;
784 c1 = maptolower[*label1++];
785 c2 = maptolower[*label2++];
786 if (c1 < c2)
787 return (-1);
788 else if (c1 > c2)
789 return (1);
790 }
791 }
792
793 /*
794 * If one name had more labels than the other, their common
795 * prefix must have been different because the shorter name
796 * ended with the root label and the longer one can't have
797 * a root label in the middle of it. Therefore, if we get
798 * to this point, the lengths must be equal.
799 */
800 INSIST(l1 == l2);
801
802 return (0);
803}

805bool
806dns_name_issubdomain(const dns_name_t *name1, const dns_name_t *name2) {
807 int order;
808 unsigned int nlabels;
809 dns_namereln_t namereln;
810
811 /*
812 * Is 'name1' a subdomain of 'name2'?
813 *
814 * Note: It makes no sense for one of the names to be relative and the
815 * other absolute. If both names are relative, then to be meaningfully
816 * compared the caller must ensure that they are both relative to the
817 * same domain.
818 */
819
820 namereln = dns_name_fullcompare(name1, name2, &order, &nlabels);
821 if (namereln == dns_namereln_subdomain ||
822 namereln == dns_namereln_equal)
823 return (true);
824
825 return (false);
826}

828bool
829dns_name_matcheswildcard(const dns_name_t *name, const dns_name_t *wname) {
830 int order;
831 unsigned int nlabels, labels;
832 dns_name_t tname;
833
834 REQUIRE(VALID_NAME(name));
835 REQUIRE(name->labels > 0);
836 REQUIRE(VALID_NAME(wname));
837 labels = wname->labels;
838 REQUIRE(labels > 0);
839 REQUIRE(dns_name_iswildcard(wname));
840
841#if defined(__clang__) && \
842 ( __clang_major__ < 3 || (__clang_major__ == 3 && __clang_minor__ < 2))
843 memset(&tname, 0, sizeof(tname));
844#endif
845 DNS_NAME_INIT(&tname, NULL);
846 dns_name_getlabelsequence(wname, 1, labels - 1, &tname);
847 if (dns_name_fullcompare(name, &tname, &order, &nlabels) ==
848 dns_namereln_subdomain)
849 return (true);
850 return (false);
851}

866void
867dns_name_getlabel(const dns_name_t *name, unsigned int n, dns_label_t *label) {
868 unsigned char *offsets;
869 dns_offsets_t odata;
870
871 /*
872 * Make 'label' refer to the 'n'th least significant label of 'name'.
873 */
874
875 REQUIRE(VALID_NAME(name));
876 REQUIRE(name->labels > 0);
877 REQUIRE(n < name->labels);
878 REQUIRE(label != NULL);
879
880 SETUP_OFFSETS(name, offsets, odata);
881
882 label->base = &name->ndata[offsets[n]];
883 if (n == name->labels - 1)
884 label->length = name->length - offsets[n];
885 else
886 label->length = offsets[n + 1] - offsets[n];
887}
888
889void
890dns_name_getlabelsequence(const dns_name_t *source,
891 unsigned int first, unsigned int n,
892 dns_name_t *target)
893{
894 unsigned char *p, l;
895 unsigned int firstoffset, endoffset;
896 unsigned int i;
897
898 /*
899 * Make 'target' refer to the 'n' labels including and following
900 * 'first' in 'source'.
901 */
902
903 REQUIRE(VALID_NAME(source));
904 REQUIRE(VALID_NAME(target));
905 REQUIRE(first <= source->labels);
906 REQUIRE(n <= source->labels - first); /* note first+n could overflow */
907 REQUIRE(BINDABLE(target));
908
909 p = source->ndata;
910 if (ISC_UNLIKELY(first == source->labels)) {
911 firstoffset = source->length;
912 } else {
913 for (i = 0; i < first; i++) {
914 l = *p;
915 p += l + 1;
916 }
917 firstoffset = (unsigned int)(p - source->ndata);
918 }
919
920 if (ISC_LIKELY(first + n == source->labels))
921 endoffset = source->length;
922 else {
923 for (i = 0; i < n; i++) {
924 l = *p;
925 p += l + 1;
926 }
927 endoffset = (unsigned int)(p - source->ndata);
928 }
929
930 target->ndata = &source->ndata[firstoffset];
931 target->length = endoffset - firstoffset;
932
933 if (first + n == source->labels && n > 0 &&
934 (source->attributes & DNS_NAMEATTR_ABSOLUTE) != 0)
935 target->attributes |= DNS_NAMEATTR_ABSOLUTE;
936 else
937 target->attributes &= ~DNS_NAMEATTR_ABSOLUTE;
938
939 target->labels = n;
940
941 /*
942 * If source and target are the same, and we're making target
943 * a prefix of source, the offsets table is correct already
944 * so we don't need to call set_offsets().
945 */
946 if (target->offsets != NULL &&
947 (target != source || first != 0))
948 set_offsets(target, target->offsets, NULL);
949}

951void
952dns_name_clone(const dns_name_t *source, dns_name_t *target) {
953
954 /*
955 * Make 'target' refer to the same name as 'source'.
956 */
957
958 REQUIRE(VALID_NAME(source));
959 REQUIRE(VALID_NAME(target));
960 REQUIRE(BINDABLE(target));
961
962 target->ndata = source->ndata;
963 target->length = source->length;
964 target->labels = source->labels;
965 target->attributes = source->attributes &
966 (unsigned int)~(DNS_NAMEATTR_READONLY | DNS_NAMEATTR_DYNAMIC |
967 DNS_NAMEATTR_DYNOFFSETS);
968 if (target->offsets != NULL && source->labels > 0) {
969 if (source->offsets != NULL)
970 memmove(target->offsets, source->offsets,
971 source->labels);
972 else
973 set_offsets(target, target->offsets, NULL);
974 }
975}

977void
978dns_name_fromregion(dns_name_t *name, const isc_region_t *r) {
979 unsigned char *offsets;
980 dns_offsets_t odata;
981 unsigned int len;
982 isc_region_t r2;
983
984 /*
985 * Make 'name' refer to region 'r'.
986 */
987
988 REQUIRE(VALID_NAME(name));
989 REQUIRE(r != NULL);
990 REQUIRE(BINDABLE(name));
991
992 INIT_OFFSETS(name, offsets, odata);
993
994 if (name->buffer != NULL) {
995 isc_buffer_clear(name->buffer);
996 isc_buffer_availableregion(name->buffer, &r2);
997 len = (r->length < r2.length) ? r->length : r2.length;
998 if (len > DNS_NAME_MAXWIRE)
999 len = DNS_NAME_MAXWIRE;
1000 if (len != 0)
1001 memmove(r2.base, r->base, len);
1002 name->ndata = r2.base;
1003 name->length = len;
1004 } else {
1005 name->ndata = r->base;
1006 name->length = (r->length <= DNS_NAME_MAXWIRE) ?
1007 r->length : DNS_NAME_MAXWIRE;
1008 }
1009
1010 if (r->length > 0)
1011 set_offsets(name, offsets, name);
1012 else {
1013 name->labels = 0;
1014 name->attributes &= ~DNS_NAMEATTR_ABSOLUTE;
1015 }
1016
1017 if (name->buffer != NULL)
1018 isc_buffer_add(name->buffer, name->length);
1019}

1033isc_result_t
1034dns_name_fromtext(dns_name_t *name, isc_buffer_t *source,
1035 const dns_name_t *origin, unsigned int options,
1036 isc_buffer_t *target)
1037{
1038 unsigned char *ndata, *label = NULL;
1039 char *tdata;
1040 char c;
1041 ft_state state;
1042 unsigned int value = 0, count = 0;
1043 unsigned int n1 = 0, n2 = 0;
1044 unsigned int tlen, nrem, nused, digits = 0, labels, tused;
1045 bool done;
1046 unsigned char *offsets;
1047 dns_offsets_t odata;
1048 bool downcase;
1049
1050 /*
1051 * Convert the textual representation of a DNS name at source
1052 * into uncompressed wire form stored in target.
1053 *
1054 * Notes:
1055 * Relative domain names will have 'origin' appended to them
1056 * unless 'origin' is NULL, in which case relative domain names
1057 * will remain relative.
1058 */
1059
1060 REQUIRE(VALID_NAME(name));
1061 REQUIRE(ISC_BUFFER_VALID(source));
1062 REQUIRE((target != NULL && ISC_BUFFER_VALID(target)) ||
1063 (target == NULL && ISC_BUFFER_VALID(name->buffer)));
1064
1065 downcase = ((options & DNS_NAME_DOWNCASE) != 0);
1066
1067 if (target == NULL && name->buffer != NULL) {
1068 target = name->buffer;
1069 isc_buffer_clear(target);
1070 }
1071
1072 REQUIRE(BINDABLE(name));
1073
1074 INIT_OFFSETS(name, offsets, odata);
1075 offsets[0] = 0;
1076
1077 /*
1078 * Make 'name' empty in case of failure.
1079 */
1080 MAKE_EMPTY(name);
1081
1082 /*
1083 * Set up the state machine.
1084 */
1085 tdata = (char *)source->base + source->current;
1086 tlen = isc_buffer_remaininglength(source);
1087 tused = 0;
1088 ndata = isc_buffer_used(target);
1089 nrem = isc_buffer_availablelength(target);
1090 if (nrem > 255)
1091 nrem = 255;
1092 nused = 0;
1093 labels = 0;
1094 done = false;
1095 state = ft_init;
1096
1097 while (nrem > 0 && tlen > 0 && !done) {
1098 c = *tdata++;
1099 tlen--;
1100 tused++;
1101
1102 switch (state) {
1103 case ft_init:
1104 /*
1105 * Is this the root name?
1106 */
1107 if (c == '.') {
1108 if (tlen != 0)
1109 return (DNS_R_EMPTYLABEL);
1110 labels++;
1111 *ndata++ = 0;
1112 nrem--;
1113 nused++;
1114 done = true;
1115 break;
1116 }
1117 if (c == '@' && tlen == 0) {
1118 state = ft_at;
1119 break;
1120 }
1121
1122 /* FALLTHROUGH */
1123 case ft_start:
1124 label = ndata;
1125 ndata++;
1126 nrem--;
1127 nused++;
1128 count = 0;
1129 if (c == '\\') {
1130 state = ft_initialescape;
1131 break;
1132 }
1133 state = ft_ordinary;
1134 if (nrem == 0)
1135 return (ISC_R_NOSPACE);
1136 /* FALLTHROUGH */
1137 case ft_ordinary:
1138 if (c == '.') {
1139 if (count == 0)
1140 return (DNS_R_EMPTYLABEL);
1141 *label = count;
1142 labels++;
1143 INSIST(labels <= 127);
1144 offsets[labels] = nused;
1145 if (tlen == 0) {
1146 labels++;
1147 *ndata++ = 0;
1148 nrem--;
1149 nused++;
1150 done = true;
1151 }
1152 state = ft_start;
1153 } else if (c == '\\') {
1154 state = ft_escape;
1155 } else {
1156 if (count >= 63)
1157 return (DNS_R_LABELTOOLONG);
1158 count++;
1159 CONVERTTOASCII(c);
1160 if (downcase)
1161 c = maptolower[c & 0xff];
1162 *ndata++ = c;
1163 nrem--;
1164 nused++;
1165 }
1166 break;
1167 case ft_initialescape:
1168 if (c == '[') {
1169 /*
1170 * This looks like a bitstring label, which
1171 * was deprecated. Intentionally drop it.
1172 */
1173 return (DNS_R_BADLABELTYPE);
1174 }
1175 state = ft_escape;
1176 POST(state);
1177 /* FALLTHROUGH */
1178 case ft_escape:
1179 if (!isdigit(c & 0xff)) {
1180 if (count >= 63)
1181 return (DNS_R_LABELTOOLONG);
1182 count++;
1183 CONVERTTOASCII(c);
1184 if (downcase)
1185 c = maptolower[c & 0xff];
1186 *ndata++ = c;
1187 nrem--;
1188 nused++;
1189 state = ft_ordinary;
1190 break;
1191 }
1192 digits = 0;
1193 value = 0;
1194 state = ft_escdecimal;
1195 /* FALLTHROUGH */
1196 case ft_escdecimal:
1197 if (!isdigit(c & 0xff))
1198 return (DNS_R_BADESCAPE);
1199 value *= 10;
1200 value += digitvalue[c & 0xff];
1201 digits++;
1202 if (digits == 3) {
1203 if (value > 255)
1204 return (DNS_R_BADESCAPE);
1205 if (count >= 63)
1206 return (DNS_R_LABELTOOLONG);
1207 count++;
1208 if (downcase)
1209 value = maptolower[value];
1210 *ndata++ = value;
1211 nrem--;
1212 nused++;
1213 state = ft_ordinary;
1214 }
1215 break;
1216 default:
1217 FATAL_ERROR(__FILE__, __LINE__,
1218 "Unexpected state %d", state);
1219 /* Does not return. */
1220 }
1221 }
1222
1223 if (!done) {
1224 if (nrem == 0)
1225 return (ISC_R_NOSPACE);
1226 INSIST(tlen == 0);
1227 if (state != ft_ordinary && state != ft_at)
1228 return (ISC_R_UNEXPECTEDEND);
1229 if (state == ft_ordinary) {
1230 INSIST(count != 0);
1231 *label = count;
1232 labels++;
1233 INSIST(labels <= 127);
1234 offsets[labels] = nused;
1235 }
1236 if (origin != NULL) {
1237 if (nrem < origin->length)
1238 return (ISC_R_NOSPACE);
1239 label = origin->ndata;
1240 n1 = origin->length;
1241 nrem -= n1;
1242 POST(nrem);
1243 while (n1 > 0) {
1244 n2 = *label++;
1245 INSIST(n2 <= 63); /* no bitstring support */
1246 *ndata++ = n2;
1247 n1 -= n2 + 1;
1248 nused += n2 + 1;
1249 while (n2 > 0) {
1250 c = *label++;
1251 if (downcase)
1252 c = maptolower[c & 0xff];
1253 *ndata++ = c;
1254 n2--;
1255 }
1256 labels++;
1257 if (n1 > 0) {
1258 INSIST(labels <= 127);
1259 offsets[labels] = nused;
1260 }
1261 }
1262 if ((origin->attributes & DNS_NAMEATTR_ABSOLUTE) != 0)
1263 name->attributes |= DNS_NAMEATTR_ABSOLUTE;
1264 }
1265 } else
1266 name->attributes |= DNS_NAMEATTR_ABSOLUTE;
1267
1268 name->ndata = (unsigned char *)target->base + target->used;
1269 name->labels = labels;
1270 name->length = nused;
1271
1272 isc_buffer_forward(source, tused);
1273 isc_buffer_add(target, name->length);
1274
1275 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
1276}

1278static void
1279free_specific(void *arg) {
1280 dns_name_totextfilter_t *mem = arg;
1281 isc_mem_put(thread_key_mctx, mem, sizeof(*mem));
1282 /* Stop use being called again. */
1283 (void)isc_thread_key_setspecific(totext_filter_proc_key, NULL);
1284}

1286static void
1287thread_key_mutex_init(void) {
1288 isc_mutex_init(&thread_key_mutex);
1289}
1290
1291static isc_result_t
1292totext_filter_proc_key_init(void) {
1293 isc_result_t result;
1294
1295 /*
1296 * We need the call to isc_once_do() to support profiled mutex
1297 * otherwise thread_key_mutex could be initialized at compile time.
1298 */
1299 result = isc_once_do(&once, thread_key_mutex_init);
1300 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
1301 return (result);
1302
1303 if (!thread_key_initialized) {
1304 LOCK(&thread_key_mutex);
1305 if (thread_key_mctx == NULL)
1306 result = isc_mem_create(0, 0, &thread_key_mctx);
1307 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
1308 goto unlock;
1309 isc_mem_setname(thread_key_mctx, "threadkey", NULL);
1310 isc_mem_setdestroycheck(thread_key_mctx, false);
1311
1312 if (!thread_key_initialized &&
1313 isc_thread_key_create(&totext_filter_proc_key,
1314 free_specific) != 0) {
1315 result = ISC_R_FAILURE;
1316 isc_mem_detach(&thread_key_mctx);
1317 } else
1318 thread_key_initialized = 1;
1319 unlock:
1320 UNLOCK(&thread_key_mutex);
1321 }
1322 return (result);
1323}

1340
1341isc_result_t
1342dns_name_totext2(const dns_name_t *name, unsigned int options,
1343 isc_buffer_t *target)
1344{
1345 unsigned char *ndata;
1346 char *tdata;
1347 unsigned int nlen, tlen;
1348 unsigned char c;
1349 unsigned int trem, count;
1350 unsigned int labels;
1351 bool saw_root = false;
1352 unsigned int oused = target->used;
1353 dns_name_totextfilter_t *mem;
1354 dns_name_totextfilter_t totext_filter_proc = NULL;
1355 isc_result_t result;
1356 bool omit_final_dot = ((options & DNS_NAME_OMITFINALDOT) != 0);
1357
1358 /*
1359 * This function assumes the name is in proper uncompressed
1360 * wire format.
1361 */
1362 REQUIRE(VALID_NAME(name));
1363 REQUIRE(ISC_BUFFER_VALID(target));
1364
1365 result = totext_filter_proc_key_init();
1366 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
1367 return (result);
1368 ndata = name->ndata;
1369 nlen = name->length;
1370 labels = name->labels;
1371 tdata = isc_buffer_used(target);
1372 tlen = isc_buffer_availablelength(target);
1373
1374 trem = tlen;
1375
1376 if (labels == 0 && nlen == 0) {
1377 /*
1378 * Special handling for an empty name.
1379 */
1380 if (trem == 0)
1381 return (ISC_R_NOSPACE);
1382
1383 /*
1384 * The names of these booleans are misleading in this case.
1385 * This empty name is not necessarily from the root node of
1386 * the DNS root zone, nor is a final dot going to be included.
1387 * They need to be set this way, though, to keep the "@"
1388 * from being trounced.
1389 */
1390 saw_root = true;
1391 omit_final_dot = false;
1392 *tdata++ = '@';
1393 trem--;
1394
1395 /*
1396 * Skip the while() loop.
1397 */
1398 nlen = 0;
1399 } else if (nlen == 1 && labels == 1 && *ndata == '\0') {
1400 /*
1401 * Special handling for the root label.
1402 */
1403 if (trem == 0)
1404 return (ISC_R_NOSPACE);
1405
1406 saw_root = true;
1407 omit_final_dot = false;
1408 *tdata++ = '.';
1409 trem--;
1410
1411 /*
1412 * Skip the while() loop.
1413 */
1414 nlen = 0;
1415 }
1416
1417 while (labels > 0 && nlen > 0 && trem > 0) {
1418 labels--;
1419 count = *ndata++;
1420 nlen--;
1421 if (count == 0) {
1422 saw_root = true;
1423 break;
1424 }
1425 if (count < 64) {
1426 INSIST(nlen >= count);
1427 while (count > 0) {
1428 c = *ndata;
1429 switch (c) {
1430 /* Special modifiers in zone files. */
1431 case 0x40: /* '@' */
1432 case 0x24: /* '$' */
1433 if ((options & DNS_NAME_MASTERFILE) == 0)
1434 goto no_escape;
1435 /* FALLTHROUGH */
1436 case 0x22: /* '"' */
1437 case 0x28: /* '(' */
1438 case 0x29: /* ')' */
1439 case 0x2E: /* '.' */
1440 case 0x3B: /* ';' */
1441 case 0x5C: /* '\\' */
1442 if (trem < 2)
1443 return (ISC_R_NOSPACE);
1444 *tdata++ = '\\';
1445 CONVERTFROMASCII(c);
1446 *tdata++ = c;
1447 ndata++;
1448 trem -= 2;
1449 nlen--;
1450 break;
1451 no_escape:
1452 default:
1453 if (c > 0x20 && c < 0x7f) {
1454 if (trem == 0)
1455 return (ISC_R_NOSPACE);
1456 CONVERTFROMASCII(c);
1457 *tdata++ = c;
1458 ndata++;
1459 trem--;
1460 nlen--;
1461 } else {
1462 if (trem < 4)
1463 return (ISC_R_NOSPACE);
1464 *tdata++ = 0x5c;
1465 *tdata++ = 0x30 +
1466 ((c / 100) % 10);
1467 *tdata++ = 0x30 +
1468 ((c / 10) % 10);
1469 *tdata++ = 0x30 + (c % 10);
1470 trem -= 4;
1471 ndata++;
1472 nlen--;
1473 }
1474 }
1475 count--;
1476 }
1477 } else {
1478 FATAL_ERROR(__FILE__, __LINE__,
1479 "Unexpected label type %02x", count);
1480 /* NOTREACHED */
1481 }
1482
1483 /*
1484 * The following assumes names are absolute. If not, we
1485 * fix things up later. Note that this means that in some
1486 * cases one more byte of text buffer is required than is
1487 * needed in the final output.
1488 */
1489 if (trem == 0)
1490 return (ISC_R_NOSPACE);
1491 *tdata++ = '.';
1492 trem--;
1493 }
1494
1495 if (nlen != 0 && trem == 0)
1496 return (ISC_R_NOSPACE);
1497
1498 if (!saw_root || omit_final_dot) {
1499 trem++;
1500 tdata--;
1501 }
1502 if (trem > 0) {
1503 *tdata = 0;
1504 }
1505 isc_buffer_add(target, tlen - trem);
1506
1507 mem = isc_thread_key_getspecific(totext_filter_proc_key);
1508 if (mem != NULL)
1509 totext_filter_proc = *mem;
1510 if (totext_filter_proc != NULL)
1511 return ((*totext_filter_proc)(target, oused));
1512
1513 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
1514}
1515
1516isc_result_t
1517dns_name_tofilenametext(const dns_name_t *name, bool omit_final_dot,
1518 isc_buffer_t *target)
1519{
1520 unsigned char *ndata;
1521 char *tdata;
1522 unsigned int nlen, tlen;
1523 unsigned char c;
1524 unsigned int trem, count;
1525 unsigned int labels;
1526
1527 /*
1528 * This function assumes the name is in proper uncompressed
1529 * wire format.
1530 */
1531 REQUIRE(VALID_NAME(name));
1532 REQUIRE((name->attributes & DNS_NAMEATTR_ABSOLUTE) != 0);
1533 REQUIRE(ISC_BUFFER_VALID(target));
1534
1535 ndata = name->ndata;
1536 nlen = name->length;
1537 labels = name->labels;
1538 tdata = isc_buffer_used(target);
1539 tlen = isc_buffer_availablelength(target);
1540
1541 trem = tlen;
1542
1543 if (nlen == 1 && labels == 1 && *ndata == '\0') {
1544 /*
1545 * Special handling for the root label.
1546 */
1547 if (trem == 0)
1548 return (ISC_R_NOSPACE);
1549
1550 omit_final_dot = false;
1551 *tdata++ = '.';
1552 trem--;
1553
1554 /*
1555 * Skip the while() loop.
1556 */
1557 nlen = 0;
1558 }
1559
1560 while (labels > 0 && nlen > 0 && trem > 0) {
1561 labels--;
1562 count = *ndata++;
1563 nlen--;
1564 if (count == 0)
1565 break;
1566 if (count < 64) {
1567 INSIST(nlen >= count);
1568 while (count > 0) {
1569 c = *ndata;
1570 if ((c >= 0x30 && c <= 0x39) || /* digit */
1571 (c >= 0x41 && c <= 0x5A) || /* uppercase */
1572 (c >= 0x61 && c <= 0x7A) || /* lowercase */
1573 c == 0x2D || /* hyphen */
1574 c == 0x5F) /* underscore */
1575 {
1576 if (trem == 0)
1577 return (ISC_R_NOSPACE);
1578 /* downcase */
1579 if (c >= 0x41 && c <= 0x5A)
1580 c += 0x20;
1581 CONVERTFROMASCII(c);
1582 *tdata++ = c;
1583 ndata++;
1584 trem--;
1585 nlen--;
1586 } else {
1587 if (trem < 4)
1588 return (ISC_R_NOSPACE);
1589 snprintf(tdata, trem, "%%%02X", c);
1590 tdata += 3;
1591 trem -= 3;
1592 ndata++;
1593 nlen--;
1594 }
1595 count--;
1596 }
1597 } else {
1598 FATAL_ERROR(__FILE__, __LINE__,
1599 "Unexpected label type %02x", count);
1600 /* NOTREACHED */
1601 }
1602
1603 /*
1604 * The following assumes names are absolute. If not, we
1605 * fix things up later. Note that this means that in some
1606 * cases one more byte of text buffer is required than is
1607 * needed in the final output.
1608 */
1609 if (trem == 0)
1610 return (ISC_R_NOSPACE);
1611 *tdata++ = '.';
1612 trem--;
1613 }
1614
1615 if (nlen != 0 && trem == 0)
1616 return (ISC_R_NOSPACE);
1617
1618 if (omit_final_dot)
1619 trem++;
1620
1621 isc_buffer_add(target, tlen - trem);
1622
1623 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
1624}

1626isc_result_t
1627dns_name_downcase(const dns_name_t *source, dns_name_t *name,
1628 isc_buffer_t *target)
1629{
1630 unsigned char *sndata, *ndata;
1631 unsigned int nlen, count, labels;
1632 isc_buffer_t buffer;
1633
1634 /*
1635 * Downcase 'source'.
1636 */
1637
1638 REQUIRE(VALID_NAME(source));
1639 REQUIRE(VALID_NAME(name));
1640 if (source == name) {
1641 REQUIRE((name->attributes & DNS_NAMEATTR_READONLY) == 0);
1642 isc_buffer_init(&buffer, source->ndata, source->length);
1643 target = &buffer;
1644 ndata = source->ndata;
1645 } else {
1646 REQUIRE(BINDABLE(name));
1647 REQUIRE((target != NULL && ISC_BUFFER_VALID(target)) ||
1648 (target == NULL && ISC_BUFFER_VALID(name->buffer)));
1649 if (target == NULL) {
1650 target = name->buffer;
1651 isc_buffer_clear(name->buffer);
1652 }
1653 ndata = (unsigned char *)target->base + target->used;
1654 name->ndata = ndata;
1655 }
1656
1657 sndata = source->ndata;
1658 nlen = source->length;
1659 labels = source->labels;
1660
1661 if (nlen > (target->length - target->used)) {
1662 MAKE_EMPTY(name);
1663 return (ISC_R_NOSPACE);
1664 }
1665
1666 while (labels > 0 && nlen > 0) {
1667 labels--;
1668 count = *sndata++;
1669 *ndata++ = count;
1670 nlen--;
1671 if (count < 64) {
1672 INSIST(nlen >= count);
1673 while (count > 0) {
1674 *ndata++ = maptolower[(*sndata++)];
1675 nlen--;
1676 count--;
1677 }
1678 } else {
1679 FATAL_ERROR(__FILE__, __LINE__,
1680 "Unexpected label type %02x", count);
1681 /* Does not return. */
1682 }
1683 }
1684
1685 if (source != name) {
1686 name->labels = source->labels;
1687 name->length = source->length;
1688 if ((source->attributes & DNS_NAMEATTR_ABSOLUTE) != 0)
1689 name->attributes = DNS_NAMEATTR_ABSOLUTE;
1690 else
1691 name->attributes = 0;
1692 if (name->labels > 0 && name->offsets != NULL)
1693 set_offsets(name, name->offsets, NULL);
1694 }
1695
1696 isc_buffer_add(target, name->length);
1697
1698 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
1699}
1700
1701static void
1702set_offsets(const dns_name_t *name, unsigned char *offsets,
1703 dns_name_t *set_name)
1704{
1705 unsigned int offset, count, length, nlabels;
1706 unsigned char *ndata;
1707 bool absolute;
1708
1709 ndata = name->ndata;
1710 length = name->length;
1711 offset = 0;
1712 nlabels = 0;
1713 absolute = false;
1714 while (ISC_LIKELY(offset != length)) {
1715 INSIST(nlabels < 128);
1716 offsets[nlabels++] = offset;
1717 count = *ndata;
1718 INSIST(count <= 63);
1719 offset += count + 1;
1720 ndata += count + 1;
1721 INSIST(offset <= length);
1722 if (ISC_UNLIKELY(count == 0)) {
1723 absolute = true;
1724 break;
1725 }
1726 }
1727 if (set_name != NULL) {
1728 INSIST(set_name == name);
1729
1730 set_name->labels = nlabels;
1731 set_name->length = offset;
1732 if (absolute)
1733 set_name->attributes |= DNS_NAMEATTR_ABSOLUTE;
1734 else
1735 set_name->attributes &= ~DNS_NAMEATTR_ABSOLUTE;
1736 }
1737 INSIST(nlabels == name->labels);
1738 INSIST(offset == name->length);
1739}

1741isc_result_t
1742dns_name_fromwire(dns_name_t *name, isc_buffer_t *source,
1743 dns_decompress_t *dctx, unsigned int options,
1744 isc_buffer_t *target)
1745{
1746 unsigned char *cdata, *ndata;
1747 unsigned int cused; /* Bytes of compressed name data used */
1748 unsigned int nused, labels, n, nmax;
1749 unsigned int current, new_current, biggest_pointer;
1750 bool done;
1751 fw_state state = fw_start;
1752 unsigned int c;
1753 unsigned char *offsets;
1754 dns_offsets_t odata;
1755 bool downcase;
1756 bool seen_pointer;
1757
1758 /*
1759 * Copy the possibly-compressed name at source into target,
1760 * decompressing it. Loop prevention is performed by checking
1761 * the new pointer against biggest_pointer.
1762 */
1763
1764 REQUIRE(VALID_NAME(name));
1765 REQUIRE((target != NULL && ISC_BUFFER_VALID(target)) ||
1766 (target == NULL && ISC_BUFFER_VALID(name->buffer)));
1767
1768 downcase = ((options & DNS_NAME_DOWNCASE) != 0);
1769
1770 if (target == NULL && name->buffer != NULL) {
1771 target = name->buffer;
1772 isc_buffer_clear(target);
1773 }
1774
1775 REQUIRE(dctx != NULL);
1776 REQUIRE(BINDABLE(name));
1777
1778 INIT_OFFSETS(name, offsets, odata);
1779
1780 /*
1781 * Make 'name' empty in case of failure.
1782 */
1783 MAKE_EMPTY(name);
1784
1785 /*
1786 * Initialize things to make the compiler happy; they're not required.
1787 */
1788 n = 0;
1789 new_current = 0;
1790
1791 /*
1792 * Set up.
1793 */
1794 labels = 0;
1795 done = false;
1796
1797 ndata = isc_buffer_used(target);
1798 nused = 0;
1799 seen_pointer = false;
1800
1801 /*
1802 * Find the maximum number of uncompressed target name
1803 * bytes we are willing to generate. This is the smaller
1804 * of the available target buffer length and the
1805 * maximum legal domain name length (255).
1806 */
1807 nmax = isc_buffer_availablelength(target);
1808 if (nmax > DNS_NAME_MAXWIRE)
1809 nmax = DNS_NAME_MAXWIRE;
1810
1811 cdata = isc_buffer_current(source);
1812 cused = 0;
1813
1814 current = source->current;
1815 biggest_pointer = current;
1816
1817 /*
1818 * Note: The following code is not optimized for speed, but
1819 * rather for correctness. Speed will be addressed in the future.
1820 */
1821
1822 while (current < source->active && !done) {
1823 c = *cdata++;
1824 current++;
1825 if (!seen_pointer)
1826 cused++;
1827
1828 switch (state) {
1829 case fw_start:
1830 if (c < 64) {
1831 offsets[labels] = nused;
1832 labels++;
1833 if (nused + c + 1 > nmax)
1834 goto full;
1835 nused += c + 1;
1836 *ndata++ = c;
1837 if (c == 0)
1838 done = true;
1839 n = c;
1840 state = fw_ordinary;
1841 } else if (c >= 128 && c < 192) {
1842 /*
1843 * 14 bit local compression pointer.
1844 * Local compression is no longer an
1845 * IETF draft.
1846 */
1847 return (DNS_R_BADLABELTYPE);
1848 } else if (c >= 192) {
1849 /*
1850 * Ordinary 14-bit pointer.
1851 */
1852 if ((dctx->allowed & DNS_COMPRESS_GLOBAL14) == 0)
1853 {
1854 return (DNS_R_DISALLOWED);
1855 }
1856 new_current = c & 0x3F;
1857 state = fw_newcurrent;
1858 } else
1859 return (DNS_R_BADLABELTYPE);
1860 break;
1861 case fw_ordinary:
1862 if (downcase)
1863 c = maptolower[c];
1864 *ndata++ = c;
1865 n--;
1866 if (n == 0)
1867 state = fw_start;
1868 break;
1869 case fw_newcurrent:
1870 new_current *= 256;
1871 new_current += c;
1872 if (new_current >= biggest_pointer)
1873 return (DNS_R_BADPOINTER);
1874 biggest_pointer = new_current;
1875 current = new_current;
1876 cdata = (unsigned char *)source->base + current;
1877 seen_pointer = true;
1878 state = fw_start;
1879 break;
1880 default:
1881 FATAL_ERROR(__FILE__, __LINE__,
1882 "Unknown state %d", state);
1883 /* Does not return. */
1884 }
1885 }
1886
1887 if (!done)
1888 return (ISC_R_UNEXPECTEDEND);
1889
1890 name->ndata = (unsigned char *)target->base + target->used;
1891 name->labels = labels;
1892 name->length = nused;
1893 name->attributes |= DNS_NAMEATTR_ABSOLUTE;
1894
1895 isc_buffer_forward(source, cused);
1896 isc_buffer_add(target, name->length);
1897
1898 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
1899
1900 full:
1901 if (nmax == DNS_NAME_MAXWIRE)
1902 /*
1903 * The name did not fit even though we had a buffer
1904 * big enough to fit a maximum-length name.
1905 */
1906 return (DNS_R_NAMETOOLONG);
1907 else
1908 /*
1909 * The name might fit if only the caller could give us a
1910 * big enough buffer.
1911 */
1912 return (ISC_R_NOSPACE);
1913}

1921
1922isc_result_t
1923dns_name_towire2(const dns_name_t *name, dns_compress_t *cctx,
1924 isc_buffer_t *target, uint16_t *comp_offsetp)
1925{
1926 unsigned int methods;
1927 uint16_t offset;
1928 dns_name_t gp; /* Global compression prefix */
1929 bool gf; /* Global compression target found */
1930 uint16_t go; /* Global compression offset */
1931 dns_offsets_t clo;
1932 dns_name_t clname;
1933
1934 /*
1935 * Convert 'name' into wire format, compressing it as specified by the
1936 * compression context 'cctx', and storing the result in 'target'.
1937 */
1938
1939 REQUIRE(VALID_NAME(name));
1940 REQUIRE(cctx != NULL);
1941 REQUIRE(ISC_BUFFER_VALID(target));
1942
1943 /*
1944 * If this exact name was already rendered before, and the
1945 * offset of the previously rendered name is passed to us, write
1946 * a compression pointer directly.
1947 */
1948 methods = dns_compress_getmethods(cctx);
1949 if (comp_offsetp != NULL && *comp_offsetp < 0x4000 &&
1950 (name->attributes & DNS_NAMEATTR_NOCOMPRESS) == 0 &&
1951 (methods & DNS_COMPRESS_GLOBAL14) != 0) {
1952 if (ISC_UNLIKELY(target->length - target->used < 2))
1953 return (ISC_R_NOSPACE);
1954 offset = *comp_offsetp;
1955 offset |= 0xc000;
1956 isc_buffer_putuint16(target, offset);
1957 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
1958 }
1959
1960 /*
1961 * If 'name' doesn't have an offsets table, make a clone which
1962 * has one.
1963 */
1964 if (name->offsets == NULL) {
1965#if defined(__clang__) && \
1966 ( __clang_major__ < 3 || (__clang_major__ == 3 && __clang_minor__ < 2))
1967 memset(&clname, 0, sizeof(clname));
1968#endif
1969 DNS_NAME_INIT(&clname, clo);
1970 dns_name_clone(name, &clname);
1971 name = &clname;
1972 }
1973 DNS_NAME_INIT(&gp, NULL);
1974
1975 offset = target->used; /*XXX*/
1976
1977 if ((name->attributes & DNS_NAMEATTR_NOCOMPRESS) == 0 &&
1978 (methods & DNS_COMPRESS_GLOBAL14) != 0)
1979 gf = dns_compress_findglobal(cctx, name, &gp, &go);
1980 else
1981 gf = false;
1982
1983 /*
1984 * If the offset is too high for 14 bit global compression, we're
1985 * out of luck.
1986 */
1987 if (gf && ISC_UNLIKELY(go >= 0x4000))
1988 gf = false;
1989
1990 /*
1991 * Will the compression pointer reduce the message size?
1992 */
1993 if (gf && (gp.length + 2) >= name->length)
1994 gf = false;
1995
1996 if (gf) {
1997 if (ISC_UNLIKELY(target->length - target->used < gp.length))
1998 return (ISC_R_NOSPACE);
1999 if (gp.length != 0) {
2000 unsigned char *base = target->base;
2001 (void)memmove(base + target->used, gp.ndata,
2002 (size_t)gp.length);
2003 }
2004 isc_buffer_add(target, gp.length);
2005 if (ISC_UNLIKELY(target->length - target->used < 2))
2006 return (ISC_R_NOSPACE);
2007 isc_buffer_putuint16(target, go | 0xc000);
2008 if (gp.length != 0) {
2009 dns_compress_add(cctx, name, &gp, offset);
2010 if (comp_offsetp != NULL)
2011 *comp_offsetp = offset;
2012 } else if (comp_offsetp != NULL) {
2013 *comp_offsetp = go;
2014 }
2015 } else {
2016 if (ISC_UNLIKELY(target->length - target->used < name->length))
2017 return (ISC_R_NOSPACE);
2018 if (name->length != 0) {
2019 unsigned char *base = target->base;
2020 (void)memmove(base + target->used, name->ndata,
2021 (size_t)name->length);
2022 }
2023 isc_buffer_add(target, name->length);
2024 dns_compress_add(cctx, name, name, offset);
2025 if (comp_offsetp != NULL)
2026 *comp_offsetp = offset;
2027 }
2028
2029 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
2030}

2032isc_result_t
2033dns_name_concatenate(const dns_name_t *prefix, const dns_name_t *suffix,
2034 dns_name_t *name, isc_buffer_t *target)
2035{
2036 unsigned char *ndata, *offsets;
2037 unsigned int nrem, labels, prefix_length, length;
2038 bool copy_prefix = true;
2039 bool copy_suffix = true;
2040 bool absolute = false;
2041 dns_name_t tmp_name;
2042 dns_offsets_t odata;
2043
2044 /*
2045 * Concatenate 'prefix' and 'suffix'.
2046 */
2047
2048 REQUIRE(prefix == NULL || VALID_NAME(prefix));
2049 REQUIRE(suffix == NULL || VALID_NAME(suffix));
2050 REQUIRE(name == NULL || VALID_NAME(name));
2051 REQUIRE((target != NULL && ISC_BUFFER_VALID(target)) ||
2052 (target == NULL && name != NULL && ISC_BUFFER_VALID(name->buffer)));
2053 if (prefix == NULL || prefix->labels == 0)
2054 copy_prefix = false;
2055 if (suffix == NULL || suffix->labels == 0)
2056 copy_suffix = false;
2057 if (copy_prefix &&
2058 (prefix->attributes & DNS_NAMEATTR_ABSOLUTE) != 0) {
2059 absolute = true;
2060 REQUIRE(!copy_suffix);
2061 }
2062 if (name == NULL) {
2063 DNS_NAME_INIT(&tmp_name, odata);
2064 name = &tmp_name;
2065 }
2066 if (target == NULL) {
2067 INSIST(name->buffer != NULL);
2068 target = name->buffer;
2069 isc_buffer_clear(name->buffer);
2070 }
2071
2072 REQUIRE(BINDABLE(name));
2073
2074 /*
2075 * Set up.
2076 */
2077 nrem = target->length - target->used;
2078 ndata = (unsigned char *)target->base + target->used;
2079 if (nrem > DNS_NAME_MAXWIRE)
2080 nrem = DNS_NAME_MAXWIRE;
2081 length = 0;
2082 prefix_length = 0;
2083 labels = 0;
2084 if (copy_prefix) {
2085 prefix_length = prefix->length;
2086 length += prefix_length;
2087 labels += prefix->labels;
2088 }
2089 if (copy_suffix) {
2090 length += suffix->length;
2091 labels += suffix->labels;
2092 }
2093 if (length > DNS_NAME_MAXWIRE) {
2094 MAKE_EMPTY(name);
2095 return (DNS_R_NAMETOOLONG);
2096 }
2097 if (length > nrem) {
2098 MAKE_EMPTY(name);
2099 return (ISC_R_NOSPACE);
2100 }
2101
2102 if (copy_suffix) {
2103 if ((suffix->attributes & DNS_NAMEATTR_ABSOLUTE) != 0)
2104 absolute = true;
2105 memmove(ndata + prefix_length, suffix->ndata, suffix->length);
2106 }
2107
2108 /*
2109 * If 'prefix' and 'name' are the same object, and the object has
2110 * a dedicated buffer, and we're using it, then we don't have to
2111 * copy anything.
2112 */
2113 if (copy_prefix && (prefix != name || prefix->buffer != target))
2114 memmove(ndata, prefix->ndata, prefix_length);
2115
2116 name->ndata = ndata;
2117 name->labels = labels;
2118 name->length = length;
2119 if (absolute)
2120 name->attributes = DNS_NAMEATTR_ABSOLUTE;
2121 else
2122 name->attributes = 0;
2123
2124 if (name->labels > 0 && name->offsets != NULL) {
2125 INIT_OFFSETS(name, offsets, odata);
2126 set_offsets(name, offsets, NULL);
2127 }
2128
2129 isc_buffer_add(target, name->length);
2130
2131 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
2132}

2164isc_result_t
2165dns_name_dup(const dns_name_t *source, isc_mem_t *mctx,
2166 dns_name_t *target)
2167{
2168 /*
2169 * Make 'target' a dynamically allocated copy of 'source'.
2170 */
2171
2172 REQUIRE(VALID_NAME(source));
2173 REQUIRE(source->length > 0);
2174 REQUIRE(VALID_NAME(target));
2175 REQUIRE(BINDABLE(target));
2176
2177 /*
2178 * Make 'target' empty in case of failure.
2179 */
2180 MAKE_EMPTY(target);
2181
2182 target->ndata = isc_mem_get(mctx, source->length);
2183 if (target->ndata == NULL)
2184 return (ISC_R_NOMEMORY);
2185
2186 memmove(target->ndata, source->ndata, source->length);
2187
2188 target->length = source->length;
2189 target->labels = source->labels;
2190 target->attributes = DNS_NAMEATTR_DYNAMIC;
2191 if ((source->attributes & DNS_NAMEATTR_ABSOLUTE) != 0)
2192 target->attributes |= DNS_NAMEATTR_ABSOLUTE;
2193 if (target->offsets != NULL) {
2194 if (source->offsets != NULL)
2195 memmove(target->offsets, source->offsets,

2463isc_result_t
2464dns_name_copy(const dns_name_t *source, dns_name_t *dest, isc_buffer_t *target) {
2465 unsigned char *ndata;
2466
2467 /*
2468 * Make dest a copy of source.
2469 */
2470
2471 REQUIRE(VALID_NAME(source));
2472 REQUIRE(VALID_NAME(dest));
2473 REQUIRE(target != NULL || dest->buffer != NULL);
2474
2475 if (target == NULL) {
2476 target = dest->buffer;
2477 isc_buffer_clear(dest->buffer);
2478 }
2479
2480 REQUIRE(BINDABLE(dest));
2481
2482 /*
2483 * Set up.
2484 */
2485 if (target->length - target->used < source->length)
2486 return (ISC_R_NOSPACE);
2487
2488 ndata = (unsigned char *)target->base + target->used;
2489 dest->ndata = target->base;
2490
2491 if (source->length != 0)
2492 memmove(ndata, source->ndata, source->length);
2493
2494 dest->ndata = ndata;
2495 dest->labels = source->labels;
2496 dest->length = source->length;
2497 if ((source->attributes & DNS_NAMEATTR_ABSOLUTE) != 0)
2498 dest->attributes = DNS_NAMEATTR_ABSOLUTE;
2499 else
2500 dest->attributes = 0;
2501
2502 if (dest->labels > 0 && dest->offsets != NULL) {
2503 if (source->offsets != NULL)
2504 memmove(dest->offsets, source->offsets, source->labels);
2505 else
2506 set_offsets(dest, dest->offsets, NULL);
2507 }
2508
2509 isc_buffer_add(target, dest->length);
2510
2511 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
2512}

2658bool
2659dns_name_istat(const dns_name_t *name) {
2660 unsigned char len;
2661 const unsigned char *ndata;
2662
2663 REQUIRE(VALID_NAME(name));
2664
2665 if (name->labels < 1)
2666 return (false);
2667
2668 ndata = name->ndata;
2669 len = ndata[0];
2670 INSIST(len <= name->length);
2671 ndata++;
2672
2673 /*
2674 * Is there at least one trust anchor reported and is the
2675 * label length consistent with a trust-anchor-telemetry label.
2676 */
2677 if ((len < 8) || (len - 3) % 5 != 0) {
2678 return (false);
2679 }
2680
2681 if (ndata[0] != '_' ||
2682 maptolower[ndata[1]] != 't' ||
2683 maptolower[ndata[2]] != 'a') {
2684 return (false);
2685 }
2686 ndata += 3;
2687 len -= 3;
2688
2689 while (len > 0) {
2690 INSIST(len >= 5);
2691 if (ndata[0] != '-' || !ishex[ndata[1]] || !ishex[ndata[2]] ||
2692 !ishex[ndata[3]] || !ishex[ndata[4]]) {
2693 return (false);
2694 }
2695 ndata += 5;
2696 len -= 5;
2697 }
2698 return (true);
2699}
